=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Emerging markets were jittery. Argentina=01,s government bonds =
fell sharply as=20
investors fretted about a default. The Brazilian real hit intra-day lows=20
against the dollar in response. Turkey=01,s lira fell after the country fai=
led=20
to persuade the IMF to release its latest tranche of funds. The Polish zlot=
y=20
and Hungarian forint also weakened. Singapore slipped into recession and it=
s=20
dollar hit an 11-year low against America=01,s.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Gloom over the River Plate E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09One cause of emerging economies=01, ills has been the strength =
of the dollar,=20
which this week hit a 16-year high in real trade-weighted terms. The dollar=
=01,s=20
rise came despite continued signs of weakness in the American economy.=20
Unemployment in June rose to 4.5%.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: The greenback's charm=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The German Institute for Economic Research published the lowest=
-yet forecast=20
for German economic growth in 2001: a sorry 1%.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: No great harm, no good either=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09A meeting of G7 finance ministers concluded on a cheerful note.=
 They stated=20
hopefully that the world economy, particularly America=01,s, would improve =
soon.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09AT&T=01,s plans to break up into four separate units began with=
 the spin-off of=20
its wireless arm. However, the company=01,s low share price prompted Comcas=
t, an=20
American cable rival, to offer $44.5 billion for AT&T Broadband, which was =
to=20
have been spun off later this year. The bid boosted AT&T=01,s shares; but t=
he=20
company said it would not sell.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Loop dreams E+
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Hold the Mayo
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09[IMAGE]
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09John Mayo was forced to resign only two weeks before he was to =
have become=20
chief executive of Marconi ,after a profit warning by the beleaguered Briti=
sh=20
telecoms-equipment company. Lord Simpson, the present chief executive, had=
=20
been expected to become non-executive chairman but will remain in place for=
=20
now. Big shareholders also want him to go soon.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09See article: Deputy heads will roll=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09The European Commission raided mobile-phone companies in Britai=
n and Germany=20
as part of an investigation into price-fixing on international charges in=
=20
both countries.=20
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Compaq Computer, the world=01,s second-biggest PC maker, gave a=
 warning that=20
profits in its latest quarter would be down sharply. America=01,s economic=
=20
slowdown has intensified competition, and troubles have spread to Europe. A=
=20
report from Merrill Lynch suggested further gloom; companies are spending=
=20
less on IT and delaying upgrades.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Microsoft is to allow PC makers more freedom to change the Wind=
ows desktop.=20
The software giant=01,s move follows an appeals court ruling criticising it=
s=20
Windows monopoly; it may thereby hope to improve its negotiating position i=
n=20
settlement talks over the government=01,s antitrust suit.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Baltimore Technologies, once one of the most admired Internet c=
ompanies, shed=20
its chief executive, Fran Rooney. The Irish Internet-security company, once=
=20
worth o5.1 billion ($8 billion), suffered a mini-collapse of its ever=20
dwindling share price that took its value to as low as o120m.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09Webvan, an American online grocer once valued at $8.7 billion, =
said that it=20
would close with the loss of 2,000 jobs. The company had slowed its losses =
by=20
abandoning extravagant expansion plans, but could not do enough to offset a=
=20
rapid decline in orders.
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09
=09=09=09=09[IMAGE]
=09=09=09=09
